# election_israel — Cursor project rules

## Project

- **Stack**: Next.js App Router (app/), React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS 4, shadcn/ui (Radix), Recharts, Framer Motion.
- **Audience & UI**: Hebrew content, RTL (`dir="rtl"`), Heebo font — preserve RTL layout, logical spacing, and accessibility when adding UI.
- **Data & copy**: Election/party/leader content lives in `lib/` and feature components — keep factual tone consistent; do not invent mandates or poll numbers without source data in code.

## Code style

- Match existing patterns: imports (`@/`), component structure, and naming in nearby files.
- Prefer small, focused changes; avoid unrelated refactors or broad formatting-only edits.
- Reuse shared pieces (`components/general/`, `components/ui/`) before adding new primitives.
- Prefer shadcn/ui components wherever possible; avoid raw/native HTML elements when an equivalent shadcn component exists.
- TypeScript: explicit types for public props and exported APIs; avoid `any` unless unavoidable.
- Keep code highly modular: split large screens/features into small, focused components with clear responsibilities.

## Next.js / React

- Default to Server Components; add `"use client"` only when hooks, browser APIs, or interactivity require it.
- Colocate route-specific UI under `app/`; feature UI under `components/<area>/`.
- Use existing API route patterns in `app/api/` when adding server endpoints.
- Maximize Next.js optimizations: use `next/image`, `next/font`, dynamic imports/code-splitting, caching/revalidation, and metadata best practices where appropriate.

## Styling

- Tailwind + existing CSS variables in `app/globals.css`; align with current spacing, typography, and color tokens.
- Avoid inline styles that fight RTL or global theme unless the file already does so.

## Assets

- Static images under `public/` (e.g. `public/parties/`, `public/leaders/`); reference with paths that work in Next/Image or `<img>` as used elsewhere.

## When answering in chat

- Use fenced code citations with line numbers and paths when referencing this repo’s code.
- Prefer concise, high-signal explanations; avoid unnecessary new markdown files unless asked.
